result.execSummary:
The defendant Quaasheem A Chambers was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Quaasheem A Chambers is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Quaasheem A Chambers was found guilty of Robbery with Use of Force [Modifiers: Party to a Crime], a class E felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.32(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Original Transcript (29 pages) SENTENCING HEARING commencing July 28, 2014, received and filed.

Defendant Quaasheem A Chambers in court with attorney Mary Garvin Guimont.  Defendant Quaasheem A Chambers in custody.  Lucy Kronforst for James Griffin appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Pursuant to plea negotiations: Count is dismissed, but read in for the purpose of sentencing, and Count 3 is dismissed outright.  As to Count 2:
Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, and further advised that if not a United States citizen deportation is possible. Defendant sworn, examined as to plea, and entered a plea of guilty.  Court found defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived all constitutional rights. Plea questionnaire waiver of rights and addendum to plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulated to the criminal complaint as factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered into the record.  The Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon not to possess any firearms/body armor.    Court further advised defendant of voting ineligibility.  Court ordered defendant REMANDED into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department.  Court ordered case adjourned for sentencing in Branch 20.  Court ordered jury trial scheduled on 07/28/2014 vacated.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for July 28, 2014 at 08:30 am.

Attorney Mary Garvin Guimont in court, defendant Quaasheem A Chambers not in court, in custody.  Lucy Kronforst appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Parties request another final pretrial date.  Final pre-trial scheduled for July 21, 2014 at 08:30 am.
